# CLAUDE-ENHANCEMENT: additive, safe to delete
#
# Context/token trimming for Claude Code's file search & reads.
# NOT a security boundary — it only reduces what Claude pulls into context.
# It does NOT hide files and does NOT protect secrets. Secret protection comes from
# permissions.deny Read rules (added in Rung 4) + the "Secrets" rule in
# docs/claude/agent-principles.md. .env is listed below only to keep it out of
# context, never as a guarantee.

# Dependencies & build output
node_modules/
dist/
dist-ssr/

# Test / tooling artifacts
test-results/
playwright-report/
blob-report/
coverage/
.vercel/

# Visual-regression baselines (~108 images — noise for code work)
baseline/
baseline-stitch-old/
current/
diff/
role-screens/

# Logs & local files
*.log
*.local

# Keep secrets out of context (NOT a security control — see note above)
.env
.env.*
